      "content": "interesting. so if you're saying nationalism is basically just a tool for oppression, what's the alternative? like, in a world where people have different values and backgrounds, how do you actually get a society to work together and follow the same rules without some kind of shared identity? is there even a realistic way to do that or is it just an impossible ideal?",
